# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# __ceil__ dict-presence — operator.contains(Cls.__dict__, '__ceil__')
#
# All 8 multiprocessing classes return false for __ceil__.
# math.ceil() delegates to __ceil__ (numbers.Real protocol), analogously to
#   __floor__. None of the 8 multiprocessing types implement numeric magnitude.
# managers._BaseSetProxy key note: set defines no __ceil__. Set cardinality is
#   obtained via len(s), not math.ceil(s). The proxy does not define __ceil__.
# managers._BaseDictProxy: dict defines no __ceil__. Dict size is len(d).
# managers.BaseListProxy: list defines no __ceil__. List length is len(l).
# multiprocessing.Process: subprocess lifecycle manager; math.ceil(process) is
#   not a meaningful Python operation.
# pool.Pool/AsyncResult/MapResult: task dispatchers and result handles;
#   no numeric magnitude is defined.
# managers.SyncManager: server process manager; math.ceil(manager) is not
#   defined.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

